A vintage 1950s style illustration of a businessman in a grey suit trapped inside a giant glass jar labeled with price tags, while outside the jar, golden coins flow upward through a funnel that narrows dramatically at the top. The scene is set against a muted olive and cream background with subtle halftone dot patterns. The businessman presses his palms against the glass with a worried expression, while shadowy corporate figures in the distance operate the funnel mechanism. The color palette features mustard yellow, burnt orange, and deep teal accents typical of mid-century advertising art.
